  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Diversified Organic Coffee Production through Community Risk Mangement in Velasco Province</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improve the productive economic base and counteract the effects of climate changes in Chiquitania communities of San Ignacio de Velasco through agricultural diversification, water mangement, and climate risk management.  

Increase income for 90 families of San Ignacio by 67% and reduce dependence on mono-cropping through agricultural diversification including 7 crops, to improve nutrition over a three year period.  

Develop risk managment plans and capacities for 120 families from 10 communities.

Strenghten the local organization MINGA to create institutional policies that will guarantee and define the rights and obligations of 600 active members over the 3 years of the project.</narrative>
  </description>
